headline: A Housing ETF Up 15.7% Despite 38% Plunge in Key Residential Demand Factor
summary: The SPDR S&P Homebuilders ETF (NYSEARCA:XHB) has climbed 15.7% year to date, trading at $119.10 per share as of February 12, 2026. The rally reflects investor optimism that easing mortgage rates and improving affordability will revive housing demand. But earnings from holdings like D.R.
